HEADWORD: Slavish
<hw>Slav"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
slaves; such as becomes or befits a slave; servile; excessively
laborious; <as>as, a <ex>slavish</ex> life; a <ex>slavish</ex>
dependance on the great.</as></def> -- <wordforms><wf>Slav"ish*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Slav"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slavism</ent>⟦br⟧
